INSTALLATION GUIDE :)

INSTALL PYTHON & VS CODE
1. Download Python
- Download here: https://www.python.org/downloads/.
- Download latest version.

2. Install Python 
- Go through installation Python.
- Check the box "Add Python to PATH".  //do this before clicking "Install Now"
- Complete the installation.

3. Verify Installation
- Open the terminal.  //for windows: "Command Prompt", for mac: "Terminal"
- Type "python --version" and press 'Enter'.
- You should see installed Python version.

4. Download VS Code
- Download here: https://code.visualstudio.com/.
- Download amd install version of your operating system.
- Complete the installation.

5. Install Python extension
- Open Visual Studio Code
- Click "Extension" icon on left sidebar.  //press (Ctrl + Shift + X) for windows
- Search for "Python" by Microsoft and install.

6. Configure Python in VS Code
- for Windows/Linux press (Ctrl + Shift + P), for Mac press (Cmd + Shift + P).
- Type "Python: Select Interpreter" and press 'Enter'.
- Choose the Python interpreter. //it will look like "Python 3.x.x"
- Open new 'terminal' in VS Code. 
- Type "python --version" to ensure it shows the Python version you installed.
